Context

Purpose:
- Compact current context for MemoryEndpoints.com work without becoming a changelog or durable memory body.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with source, reports, and the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: compact project context, current objective shape, and active constraints.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this file when the compact current context changes; preserve detail in durable docs, reports, or MATM.
Source of truth: `.uai/identity.uai`, `.uai/overview.uai`, `.uai/progress.uai`, and current repository state.
Next action for agents: use this as a compact orientation, then load the specialized typed file before acting on a topic.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, private customer data, or private deployment values.

Current context:
- The active goal is to move the reports in `D:\DownloadArchive` into the database-backed MemoryEndpoints.com knowledge system one source at a time, creating context-rich company, workspace, and project wiki trees while improving the system through dogfooding.
- The repository has working local route, storage, package, secret-scan, `.uai`, static-site, and dogfood evidence.
- Latest-code MemoryEndpoints.com public deployment is verified through the FileZilla-backed explicit FTPS profile; MultiAgentMemory.com companion publishing is also live-verified through its FileZilla-backed FTPS profile.
- The database wiki has lifecycle-aware pages and first-class external-link search for `AI Agent Memory Architecture Research.md`, `AI Agent Memory Best Practices Research.md`, `MATM Architecture Design Research.md`, `AI Memory Governance Feedback Loop.md`, and `AI Dreaming Memory Management for LLMWikis.org.md`.
- `AI Agent Memory Best Practices Research.md` is represented by one canonical current contract, one complete historical source, and nine focused pages. Its 46 numbered bibliography records were ingested one at a time, four independent authority records supplement review, and lifecycle labels distinguish current contracts, historical surveys, and unverified proposals.
- Source preflight is mandatory before every report or external-link write. Request fingerprints include the indexed body so exact replays remain idempotent while changed content creates a revision; report text omits embedded data images while retaining exact source, selection, and indexed-content hashes.
- Independent review corrected the source's model attribution and unsupported decay implications before promotion. Vendor evidence remains labeled as first-party evidence, weak/community evidence remains unreviewed, and repeated representations of one study are not counted as independent sources.
- The knowledge surface is private by invariant: `/knowledge` is only an empty authentication shell, all wiki/search/external-link data requires a workspace-bound key, and durable knowledge belongs only to company, workspace, or project. Accounts/users are many-to-many company members and do not own knowledge trees.
- The ingestion tool accepts rendered Markdown headings whose source punctuation is backslash-escaped; regression tests cover the behavior.
- The ingestion tool ignores ATX-looking headings inside fenced and indented code so embedded schema examples remain within their real report section; full local, aggregate, exact-SHA deployment, production MySQL, combined dogfood, and human-wiki verification pass.
- Local dogfood selects an isolated SQLite database explicitly instead of inheriting the production MySQL profile through the obsolete JSON-store environment path. Fresh command evidence satisfies readiness only after a successful check, while tracked evidence remains the fallback.
- The `.uai` suite remains active memory and forbidden duration/state filenames are not allowed under any purpose.
- Active handoff buckets must be empty or placeholder-only after processed intake is archived or otherwise dispositioned.
